rComments: Good prof.. interesting and fun, but the readings were boring and way too expensive.

so kind and intelligent. he really was a joy to take a class from.  he gave excellent feedback on papers, and genuinely loves his subject, and wants you to love it too. if you get the chance, take one of his courses.

Good teacher, explains things well and clearly, but you will be reading a lot to supplement the lectures. If you read all the readings, the lectures become somewhat unnecessary though, still they are a good 'outline' of the most important points. The course is a good fundamental for anyone going into history.

a lot of reading, 3 textbooks which are pricey, easy course- covers a wide range of history- mainly keeps to Germany, Poland, France, Italy, England... Cook doesnt cover Spain, but it very well spoken and interesting to listen to although going to his lectures isnt really necessary
